<subSubSection id="C31134C9FF9CFFAFF4FCFD05FACBCDEC" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB46742FF9CFFAFF4FCFD05FAF5C849" blockId="3.[151,1437,651,1038]" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF4FCFD05FEFCC9B5" bold="true" box="[151,266,651,678]" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(based on adults). With the following combination of characters: adults with only three setae on the palp genu (unique); lacking series of spine-like setae latero-ventrally on the idiosoma; metapodal shields with acute postero-lateral angles (unique); setae 
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF67CFD5AFDC8C9FD" box="[535,574,724,750]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Jv5</emphasis>
inserted posterior to the fusion line of the ventral and anal shields; with one pair of greatly elongated setae inserted on the postero-marginal shield. Female with a strip-like sclerite between the geniti-ventral and the endopodal-sternal shield remnants; sternal setae 
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF7C3FC92FC3CC825" box="[936,970,796,822]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">st3</emphasis>
inserted on soft cuticle. Male with sternal setae 
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF4BDFCCEFF01C849" box="[214,247,832,858]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">st3</emphasis>
on endopodal-sternal shield remnants (unique); seta 
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF723FCCEFC9AC849" box="[840,876,832,858]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">pl1</emphasis>
on femora II hook-like and spinose.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB46742FF9CFFAFF4ACFCEDFD49CF1D" blockId="3.[151,1437,651,1038]" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF4ACFCEDFD52C86D" bold="true" box="[199,676,867,894]" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Comparisons with related taxa (adults).</emphasis>
Based on literature data and the collections of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF0D0FCEAFA76C86D" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1892" box="[1211,1408,868,894]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Heterozerconidae</taxonomicName>
at the OSAL, there are at least two genera of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF607FC06FCC7C8B1" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1892" box="[620,817,904,930]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Heterozerconidae</taxonomicName>
in S.E. Asia. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF7ACFC06FBC9C8B1" box="[967,1087,904,930]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Allozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF7ACFC06FBC9C8B1" box="[967,1087,904,930]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Allozercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found throughout the region, while 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF4B4FC22FE69C8D5" authority="Gerdeman &amp; Garcia &amp; Herczak &amp; Klompen, 2018" authorityName="Gerdeman &amp; Garcia &amp; Herczak &amp; Klompen" authorityYear="2018" box="[223,415,940,966]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Philippinozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF4B4FC22FE69C8D5" box="[223,415,940,966]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Philippinozercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
so far has only been found in the 
<collectingCountry id="F31C27D2FF9CFFAFF75AFC22FC45C8D5" box="[817,947,940,966]" name="Philippines" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Philippines</collectingCountry>
. The two genera can, and occasionally do, co-occur on a single host individual. They are probably closely related, sharing a number of characters relative to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF4FCFC7AFEAACF1D" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1892" box="[151,348,1012,1038]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Heterozerconidae</taxonomicName>
from Africa or the New World:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB46742FF9CFFAFF4FCFBB8FEB1CF63" blockId="3.[151,1437,1078,1565]" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">
1. setae 
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF56DFBB8FED1CF43" box="[262,295,1078,1104]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">
st 
<quantity id="4CF3CAA7FF9CFFAFF572FBB8FED1CF43" box="[281,295,1078,1104]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" unit="in" value="3.0">3</quantity>
</emphasis>
in the female on shieldlets that are not fused to the geniti-ventral shield (vs. inserted on the geniti-ventral shield).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB46742FF9CFFAFF4FCFBFAFD0DCFBE" blockId="3.[151,1437,1078,1565]" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">
2. setae 
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF56DFBFAFED1CF9D" box="[262,295,1140,1166]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">
st 
<quantity id="4CF3CAA7FF9CFFAFF570FBFAFED1CF9D" box="[283,295,1140,1166]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" unit="in" value="1.0">1</quantity>
</emphasis>
in the male on a contiguous endopodal shield (vs. on separate shieldlets with lyrifissure 
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF168FBFAFAD3CF9D" box="[1283,1317,1140,1166]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">
<date id="FFB54182FF9CFFAFF168FBFAFAD3CF9D" box="[1283,1317,1140,1166]" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">iv1</date>
</emphasis>
only (
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF105FBFAFEA1CFBF" authorityName="Fain" authorityYear="1989" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Amheterozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF105FBFAFEA1CFBF" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Amheterozercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF50EFB1CFDB0CFBF" authorityName="Gerdeman &amp; Klompen" authorityYear="2003" box="[357,582,1170,1196]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Narceoheterozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF50EFB1CFDB0CFBF" box="[357,582,1170,1196]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Narceoheterozercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF63EFB1DFD1DCFBF" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1888" box="[597,747,1171,1196]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Heterozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF63EFB1DFD1DCFBF" box="[597,747,1171,1196]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Heterozercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB46742FF9CFFAFF4FCFB3FFD17CFF9" blockId="3.[151,1437,1078,1565]" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">
3. setae 
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF56CFB3FFED1CFD8" box="[263,295,1201,1227]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">
st 
<quantity id="4CF3CAA7FF9CFFAFF571FB3FFED1CFD8" box="[282,295,1201,1227]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" unit="in" value="2.0">2</quantity>
</emphasis>
in the male on distinct endopodal shield (shared with 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF7E1FB3FFBC9CFD8" authorityName="Fain" authorityYear="1989" box="[906,1087,1201,1227]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Amheterozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF7E1FB3FFBC9CFD8" box="[906,1087,1201,1227]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Amheterozercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), vs. free (
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF0D1FB3CFAA6CFD8" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1888" box="[1210,1360,1202,1227]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Heterozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF0D1FB3CFAA6CFD8" box="[1210,1360,1202,1227]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Heterozercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or on the sterniti-ventral shield (
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF584FB5EFD26CFF9" authorityName="Gerdeman &amp; Klompen" authorityYear="2003" box="[495,720,1232,1258]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Narceoheterozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF584FB5EFD26CFF9" box="[495,720,1232,1258]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Narceoheterozercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB46742FF9CFFAFF4ACFB61FE0ECE34" blockId="3.[151,1437,1078,1565]" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">
Note: Characters 2–3 cannot be coded for 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF6C4FB61FCA7CE1B" authorityName="Fain" authorityYear="1989" box="[687,849,1263,1288]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Maracazercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF6C4FB61FCA7CE1B" box="[687,849,1263,1288]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Maracazercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF7E7FB60FBBBCE1B" authorityName="Fain" authorityYear="1989" box="[908,1101,1262,1288]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Afroheterozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF7E7FB60FBBBCE1B" box="[908,1101,1262,1288]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Afroheterozercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which have fused endopodal and sterniti-ventral shields.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB46742FF9CFFAFF4FCFAA2FE39CE76" blockId="3.[151,1437,1078,1565]" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">
4. lateral opisthosomal setae not modified (vs. distinctly modified in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF7DBFAA2FB93CE55" authorityName="Fain" authorityYear="1989" box="[944,1125,1324,1350]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Amheterozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF7DBFAA2FB93CE55" box="[944,1125,1324,1350]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Amheterozercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF01FFAA2FAE0CE56" authorityName="Fain" authorityYear="1989" box="[1140,1302,1324,1349]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Maracazercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF01FFAA2FAE0CE56" box="[1140,1302,1324,1349]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Maracazercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF14EFAA2FF19CE77" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1888" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Heterozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF14EFAA2FF19CE77" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Heterozercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF495FAC4FE49CE77" authorityName="Fain" authorityYear="1989" box="[254,447,1354,1380]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Afroheterozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF495FAC4FE49CE77" box="[254,447,1354,1380]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Afroheterozercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB46742FF9CFFAFF4FCFAE6FAF0CE97" blockId="3.[151,1437,1078,1565]" box="[151,1286,1384,1412]" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">
5. setae 
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF56DFAE7FEDBCE90" box="[262,301,1385,1411]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Jv5</emphasis>
inserted posterior to fusion line of the ventral and anal shields (vs. anterior to that line).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB46742FF9CFFAFF4FCFA09FCB4CED2" blockId="3.[151,1437,1078,1565]" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">
6. seta 
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF492FA06FED7CEB1" box="[249,289,1416,1442]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">pv1</emphasis>
on genua and tibiae II of male spinose (vs. setiform). Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF7B1FA06FB86CEB2" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1888" box="[986,1136,1416,1441]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Heterozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF7B1FA06FB86CEB2" box="[986,1136,1416,1441]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Heterozercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a spinose ventral seta on genu and tibiae II, but this appears to be 
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF6D9FA28FD2CCED3" box="[690,730,1446,1472]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">av1</emphasis>
, not 
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF778FA28FCCACED3" box="[787,828,1446,1472]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">pv1</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB46742FF9CFFAFF4FCFA4BFB88CD08" blockId="3.[151,1437,1078,1565]" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">
7. both genera may share tocospermous, rather than podospermous, mating systems (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A1AB3FF9CFFAFF007FA4BFA92CECC" author="Di Palma, A. &amp; de Moraes, G. J. &amp; Gerdeman, B. S. &amp; Huber, S. &amp; Kitajima, E. W. &amp; Alberti, G." box="[1132,1380,1476,1503]" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" pagination="639 - 655" refId="ref8723" refString="Di Palma, A., de Moraes, G. J., Gerdeman, B. S., Huber, S., Kitajima, E. W. &amp; Alberti, G. (2015) Ultrastructural and functional adaptations of the female reproductive system in the family Heterozerconidae (Acari, Anactinotrichida, Gamasida, Heterozerconina) and implications for the systematic position of the group. Arthropod Structure &amp; Development, 44 (6, Part B), 639 - 655. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. asd. 2015.09.002" type="journal article" year="2015">
Di Palma 
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF08BFA48FAE4CECC" box="[1248,1298,1477,1503]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">et al</emphasis>
., 2015
</bibRefCitation>
), despite the presence of a spermatodactyl in the males. This characteristic is tentative, it has only been examined in detail in one Asian and two American species. It clearly needs to be studied in more taxa.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB46742FF9CFFAFF4FCF9C4FC75CD77" blockId="3.[151,1436,1610,1791]" box="[151,899,1610,1637]" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF4FCF9C4FEA1CD77" authority="Gerdeman &amp; Garcia &amp; Herczak &amp; Klompen, 2018" authorityName="Gerdeman &amp; Garcia &amp; Herczak &amp; Klompen" authorityYear="2018" box="[151,343,1610,1636]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Philippinozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF4FCF9C4FEA1CD77" box="[151,343,1610,1636]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Philippinozercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be differentiated from 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF6E3F9C4FCF6CD77" box="[648,768,1610,1636]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Allozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF6E3F9C4FCF6CD77" box="[648,768,1610,1636]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Allozercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB46742FF9CFFAFF4FCF9E7FDD5CDB1" blockId="3.[151,1436,1610,1791]" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">
1. the presence of a strip-like sclerite between the geniti-ventral and the endopodal-sternal shield remnants in the females (absent in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF5F1F906FDE4CDB1" box="[410,530,1672,1698]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Allozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF5F1F906FDE4CDB1" box="[410,530,1672,1698]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Allozercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB46742FF9CFFAFF4FCF928FB55CDD3" blockId="3.[151,1436,1610,1791]" box="[151,1187,1702,1729]" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">
2. the acute postero-lateral angle of the metapodal shields (rounded in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF7ABF928FBCECDD3" box="[960,1080,1702,1728]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Allozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF7ABF928FBCECDD3" box="[960,1080,1702,1728]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Allozercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), unique.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB46742FF9CFFAFF4FCF94BFB83CDCC" blockId="3.[151,1436,1610,1791]" box="[151,1141,1733,1759]" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">3. the reduction in setal complement of the palp genu in the adults from 6 to 3, unique.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB46742FF9CFFAFF4FCF96AFACBCDEC" blockId="3.[151,1436,1610,1791]" box="[151,1341,1763,1791]" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">
4. the shape of seta 
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF5E3F96AFE5ACDED" box="[392,428,1764,1790]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">pl1</emphasis>
on femora II of the male: hook-like and spinose (vs. a straight spine or setiform).
</paragraph>
